# CONCRETE PLAN: All-Core Dual-NoC 3-Hop Gather/Scatter Benchmark (Blackhole)

All file:line citations below were re-verified against `/home/starboy/tt-metal`. I recommend the **classic `CreateKernel` + `DataMovementConfig` path** (not Metal-2.0 `ProgramSpec`), because the classic API is the only one in the repo that demonstrably places two RISCs on one core each bound to a different NoC in the same program (`core_bidirectional/test_core_bidirectional.cpp:93-144`) and that drives both NoCs concurrently (`noc/test_dynamic_noc.cpp:75-93`). The Metal-2.0 `ProgramSpec` path used by `all_to_all` (`test_all_to_all.cpp:139-148`) hard-binds exactly one `gen1_config.processor`+`.noc` per `KernelSpec`, so dual-NoC would require two `KernelSpec`s and is more friction.

## Core design decisions (derived from extractions + verified source)

- **Dual-NoC concurrency**: two kernels per core. `writer.cpp` on `RISCV_0` bound to `NOC::NOC_0` (does the SCATTER, X-then-Y east/south via `noc_async_write`). `reader.cpp` on `RISCV_1` bound to `NOC::NOC_1` (does the GATHER, Y-then-X north/west via `noc_async_read`). This is exactly the core_bidirectional split (`test_core_bidirectional.cpp:97-99` RISCV_0/NOC_0; `:141-143` RISCV_1) and the dynamic_noc dual-launch (`test_dynamic_noc.cpp:80-92`).
- **Direction = NoC choice, NOT coordinate math**: On Blackhole, `DYNAMIC_NOC_X/Y` are identity macros (`blackhole/noc_nonblocking_api.h:44-45`), so `get_noc_addr(x,y,addr)` returns the *same* packed address for both NoCs (`dataflow_api_addrgen.h:212-215`). You pass **physical NoC-0 coords for both NoCs**; the X-then-Y(NOC0)/Y-then-X(NOC1) routing is the hardware property. Do NOT mirror coords. This is the single biggest correctness gotcha.
- **3-hop partner**: computed **host-side** per core from logical coords, converted with `device->worker_core_from_logical_core(...)` (the canonical mapping at `dm_common.cpp:28`, `test_all_to_all.cpp:97`), passed per-core as runtime args. NOC0 partner = +3 in dimension-order travel direction (east/south); NOC1 partner = the north/west +3 partner. "3-hop" = Manhattan distance 3 between the logical core and its partner.
- **Single end-of-loop barrier per NoC** (per the BW gotcha: a per-iteration barrier serializes and measures latency, not BW — `noc_read.cpp:26-27` is the anti-pattern). Each kernel issues all transactions then ONE barrier inside the `DeviceZoneScopedN` zone (matches `sender.cpp:51`, `requestor.cpp:51`).
- **Blackhole specifics**: page size 64B (`dm_common.cpp:21`), max transaction 16384B single-packet fast path (`noc_parameters.h:287-290`), NOC width 64 B/cyc/NoC (`constants.py:11`). Add explicit flush before any cross-core signal (BH ND-mismatch warning, `BlackholeBringUpProgrammingGuide.md:95`).
- **Per-core bytes stamp is mandatory** here: gather and scatter move different byte counts per core and edge cores have fewer valid partners, so stamp `DeviceTimestampedData("Per-core bytes", ...)` or `stats_collector.py:221-224` will over/under-count `total_bytes`.

---

## (1) KERNELS

### `tests/tt_metal/tt_metal/data_movement/gather_scatter_3hop/kernels/writer.cpp`
RISCV_0 / NOC_0 — SCATTER (push local L1 → partner L1, east/south X-then-Y). Based on `all_to_all/kernels/sender.cpp:9-60`.

```cpp
// SPDX-FileCopyrightText: © 2026 Tenstorrent USA, Inc.
// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0
#include "api/dataflow/dataflow_api.h"
#include "api/debug/dprint.h"
#include "ckernel.h"

// Dual-NoC 3-hop SCATTER on NOC0 (X-then-Y, east/south). Runs on RISCV_0.
void kernel_main() {
    // Compile-time args (constexpr; see all_to_all/kernels/sender.cpp:11-17)
    constexpr uint32_t test_id          = get_compile_time_arg_val(0);
    constexpr uint32_t src_l1_base       = get_compile_time_arg_val(1); // local scatter source
    constexpr uint32_t dst_l1_base       = get_compile_time_arg_val(2); // remote partner sink
    constexpr uint32_t num_of_transactions = get_compile_time_arg_val(3);
    constexpr uint32_t bytes_per_transaction = get_compile_time_arg_val(4);
    constexpr uint32_t num_partners      = get_compile_time_arg_val(5); // 3-hop partners (NOC0 dir)
    constexpr uint32_t num_virtual_channels = get_compile_time_arg_val(6);

    const uint32_t src_addr = src_l1_base;
    const uint32_t dst_addr = dst_l1_base;
    uint32_t per_core_bytes = 0;

    {
        DeviceZoneScopedN("RISCV0");
        for (uint32_t j = 0; j < num_partners; j++) {
            // Physical NOC-0 coords supplied by host (same coords used for both NoCs on BH).
            uint32_t partner_x = get_arg_val<uint32_t>(j * 2);
            uint32_t partner_y = get_arg_val<uint32_t>(j * 2 + 1);
            // Sentinel 0xFFFFFFFF => no valid 3-hop partner this direction (edge core); skip.
            if (partner_x == 0xFFFFFFFF) { continue; }

            // get_noc_addr packs physical x,y + L1 offset; NOC0 routes X-then-Y in HW.
            uint64_t dst_noc_addr = get_noc_addr(partner_x, partner_y, dst_addr);

            for (uint32_t i = 0; i < num_of_transactions; i++) {
                uint32_t vc = i % num_virtual_channels;
                // NOC_0 is the implicit noc_index because host bound this kernel to RISCV_0/NOC_0.
                noc_async_write(src_addr, dst_noc_addr, bytes_per_transaction, noc_index, vc);
            }
            per_core_bytes += num_of_transactions * bytes_per_transaction;
        }
        noc_async_write_barrier();  // single drain inside the timed zone
    }

    DeviceTimestampedData("Test id", test_id);
    DeviceTimestampedData("NoC Index", noc_index);              // = 0
    DeviceTimestampedData("Number of transactions", num_of_transactions * num_partners);
    DeviceTimestampedData("Transaction size in bytes", bytes_per_transaction);
    DeviceTimestampedData("Number of Virtual Channels", num_virtual_channels);
    DeviceTimestampedData("Per-core bytes", per_core_bytes);    // REQUIRED: asymmetric traffic
}
```

### `tests/tt_metal/tt_metal/data_movement/gather_scatter_3hop/kernels/reader.cpp`
RISCV_1 / NOC_1 — GATHER (pull partner L1 → local L1, north/west Y-then-X). Based on `all_from_all/kernels/requestor.cpp:9-62`.

```cpp
// SPDX-FileCopyrightText: © 2026 Tenstorrent USA, Inc.
// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0
#include "api/dataflow/dataflow_api.h"
#include "api/debug/dprint.h"
#include "ckernel.h"

// Dual-NoC 3-hop GATHER on NOC1 (Y-then-X, north/west). Runs on RISCV_1.
void kernel_main() {
    constexpr uint32_t test_id          = get_compile_time_arg_val(0);
    constexpr uint32_t dst_l1_base       = get_compile_time_arg_val(1); // local gather sink
    constexpr uint32_t src_l1_base       = get_compile_time_arg_val(2); // remote partner source
    constexpr uint32_t num_of_transactions = get_compile_time_arg_val(3);
    constexpr uint32_t bytes_per_transaction = get_compile_time_arg_val(4);
    constexpr uint32_t num_partners      = get_compile_time_arg_val(5); // 3-hop partners (NOC1 dir)
    constexpr uint32_t num_virtual_channels = get_compile_time_arg_val(6);

    const uint32_t dst_addr = dst_l1_base;
    const uint32_t src_addr = src_l1_base;
    uint32_t per_core_bytes = 0;

    {
        DeviceZoneScopedN("RISCV1");
        for (uint32_t j = 0; j < num_partners; j++) {
            uint32_t partner_x = get_arg_val<uint32_t>(j * 2);
            uint32_t partner_y = get_arg_val<uint32_t>(j * 2 + 1);
            if (partner_x == 0xFFFFFFFF) { continue; }

            uint64_t src_noc_addr = get_noc_addr(partner_x, partner_y, src_addr);

            for (uint32_t i = 0; i < num_of_transactions; i++) {
                uint32_t vc = i % num_virtual_channels;
                // noc_index here = 1 because host bound this kernel to RISCV_1/NOC_1.
                noc_async_read(src_noc_addr, dst_addr, bytes_per_transaction, noc_index, vc);
            }
            per_core_bytes += num_of_transactions * bytes_per_transaction;
        }
        noc_async_read_barrier();  // single drain inside the timed zone
    }

    DeviceTimestampedData("Test id", test_id);
    DeviceTimestampedData("NoC Index", noc_index);              // = 1
    DeviceTimestampedData("Number of transactions", num_of_transactions * num_partners);
    DeviceTimestampedData("Transaction size in bytes", bytes_per_transaction);
    DeviceTimestampedData("Number of Virtual Channels", num_virtual_channels);
    DeviceTimestampedData("Per-core bytes", per_core_bytes);    // REQUIRED
}
```

API signatures verified: `noc_async_write` (`dataflow_api.h:827-833`), `noc_async_read` (`dataflow_api.h:551-557`), `noc_async_write_barrier` (`:1766`), `noc_async_read_barrier` (`:1737`), `get_noc_addr(x,y,addr)` (`dataflow_api_addrgen.h:212`).

