## (2) HOST PROGRAM STRUCTURE

`tests/tt_metal/tt_metal/data_movement/gather_scatter_3hop/test_gather_scatter_3hop.cpp`. Skeleton (classic API, all-core, dual-NoC):

```cpp
// Fixture: GenericMeshDeviceFixture (fast-dispatch); device per all DM tests.
IDevice* device = mesh_device->impl().get_device(0);                  // dm_common.cpp:26, test_all_to_all.cpp:59

// ---- ALL-CORE grid over the FULL compute grid ----
CoreCoord grid = device->compute_with_storage_grid_size();            // 120 Tensix on BH; test_all_to_all.cpp:446
CoreRange all_cores({0,0}, {grid.x - 1, grid.y - 1});                 // test_noc_rtor.cpp:158-160 pattern
CoreRangeSet all_core_set({all_cores});

// ---- L1 layout (non-overlapping carve-out) ----
auto [bytes_per_page, max_bytes, max_pages] =
    unit_tests::dm::compute_physical_constraints(mesh_device);        // 64B page on BH; dm_common.cpp:47-58
uint32_t bytes_per_transaction = pages_per_transaction * bytes_per_page;
L1AddressInfo l1 = unit_tests::dm::get_l1_address_and_size(mesh_device, {0,0}); // dm_common.cpp:23-35
uint32_t scatter_src_addr = l1.base_address;                          // writer reads here
uint32_t scatter_dst_addr = scatter_src_addr + bytes_per_transaction; // writer writes remote here
uint32_t gather_dst_addr  = scatter_dst_addr + bytes_per_transaction; // reader writes local here
uint32_t gather_src_addr  = gather_dst_addr  + bytes_per_transaction; // reader reads remote here
// require l1.size >= 4 * bytes_per_transaction (directed-ideal must divide max_pages by ~4)

Program program = CreateProgram();

// ---- Two kernels, one per NoC, over the SAME all-core set ----
std::vector<uint32_t> writer_cta = {test_id, scatter_src_addr, scatter_dst_addr,
                                    num_of_transactions, bytes_per_transaction,
                                    MAX_PARTNERS /*=3-hop dir count*/, num_vc};
auto writer = CreateKernel(program, ".../kernels/writer.cpp", all_core_set,
    DataMovementConfig{.processor=DataMovementProcessor::RISCV_0,
                       .noc=NOC::NOC_0, .compile_args=writer_cta});      // core_bidirectional:93-100

std::vector<uint32_t> reader_cta = {test_id, gather_dst_addr, gather_src_addr,
                                    num_of_transactions, bytes_per_transaction,
                                    MAX_PARTNERS, num_vc};
auto reader = CreateKernel(program, ".../kernels/reader.cpp", all_core_set,
    DataMovementConfig{.processor=DataMovementProcessor::RISCV_1,
                       .noc=NOC::NOC_1, .compile_args=reader_cta});      // core_bidirectional:137-144

// ---- Per-core 3-hop partner derivation + runtime args ----
for (auto& c : corerange_to_cores(all_core_set)) {
    // NOC0 = X-then-Y east/south 3-hop: travel +3 manhattan toward +x then +y, clamp to grid.
    std::vector<uint32_t> writer_rt = make_3hop_partners(device, grid, c, /*east_south=*/true);
    // NOC1 = Y-then-X north/west 3-hop: travel toward -y then -x.
    std::vector<uint32_t> reader_rt = make_3hop_partners(device, grid, c, /*east_south=*/false);
    SetRuntimeArgs(program, writer, c, writer_rt);                     // test_dynamic_noc.cpp:143
    SetRuntimeArgs(program, reader, c, reader_rt);
}
// make_3hop_partners(): for each logical partner at 3-hop offset that stays on-grid,
//   CoreCoord phys = device->worker_core_from_logical_core(partner_logical);  // test_all_to_all.cpp:97
//   push phys.x, phys.y (flat pairs, like sub_worker_coordinates test_all_to_all.cpp:98-99)
//   off-grid slot => push 0xFFFFFFFF,0xFFFFFFFF sentinel (kernel skips).

program.set_runtime_id(unit_tests::dm::runtime_host_id++);            // dm_common.cpp:18, test_all_to_all.cpp:178

// ---- seed L1 + single launch + single barrier ----
for (auto& c : corerange_to_cores(all_core_set)) {                   // test_all_to_all.cpp:193-196
    detail::WriteToDeviceL1(device, c, scatter_src_addr, packed_input);
    detail::WriteToDeviceL1(device, c, gather_src_addr,  packed_input); // pre-seed gather source
}
MetalContext::instance().get_cluster().l1_barrier(device->id());

auto mesh_workload = distributed::MeshWorkload();
mesh_workload.add_program(distributed::MeshCoordinateRange(distributed::MeshCoordinate({0,0})),
                          std::move(program));                        // test_all_to_all.cpp:199-203
auto& cq = mesh_device->mesh_command_queue();

// ===== HOOK POINT A: snapshot bhtop 0x200 NIU flit counters HERE (before enqueue) =====
distributed::EnqueueMeshWorkload(cq, mesh_workload, false);          // test_all_to_all.cpp:206
Finish(cq);                                                          // single end-of-loop barrier
// ===== HOOK POINT B: snapshot bhtop 0x200 NIU flit counters HERE (after Finish) =====
```

The 0x200 NIU flit-counter snapshots bracket `EnqueueMeshWorkload`→`Finish` (the only host sync point), giving the third, independent BW number (see §5). Read-back/equality is optional for a pure BW run (the C++ side never computes BW; `test_all_to_all.cpp:214-227` only does correctness).

